=Episode 3=

11
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:47,800
Hello, that's all.

12
00:01:11,060 --> 00:01:11,980
What's the matter?

13
00:01:12,460 --> 00:01:14,500
Showing off your drinking capacity?

14
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:17,780
Guess you picked that up at the pub.

15
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:19,460
I can hear it in your tone.

16
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:22,300
You're mocking me
for having too much fun.

17
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,300
How could I dare mock you?

18
00:01:25,060 --> 00:01:27,380
- I only serve...
- "I only serve Chairman Cen."

19
00:01:27,820 --> 00:01:30,020
"Let your admirers handle your affairs."

20
00:01:32,020 --> 00:01:33,940
I've heard this reasoning
countless times.

21
00:01:34,660 --> 00:01:35,780
Can you try

22
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,380
something new?

23
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:39,180
Mr. Cen.

24
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,540
Don't call me Mr. Cen.

25
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:43,580
- Cen Siyuan.
- Stop that.

26
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,180
Don't smile.

27
00:01:57,820 --> 00:01:58,980
Are you

28
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:01,860
arguing with Miss Su again?

29
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:05,740
Unlike someone,
Peipei doesn't fuss over every detail.

30
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:07,980
Besides,

31
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,180
I can always buy some gifts.

32
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:11,620
Exactly.

33
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:13,900
In your eyes,

34
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:15,380
the problems

35
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:17,540
that gifts and money can solve
aren't problems.

36
00:02:17,540 --> 00:02:18,380
Isn't that right?

37
00:02:18,620 --> 00:02:20,780
Isn't that how you handle things
with my mother too?

38
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,440
Wasn't it you who mentioned
the bonus and insurance yesterday?

39
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,500
How about this?

40
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:31,320
I'll hire you as a part-timer.

41
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:33,460
It's sure to be more
than what my mother gave you.

42
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:35,160
You just help me come up with a plan.

43
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,500
Put together a PPT for me

44
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:38,180
to win Peipei's favor,

45
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,140
so she won't ever want to leave me.

46
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:43,900
You can also make up for yesterday.

47
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:53,660
Alright.

48
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:56,500
Who can say no to money?

49
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:58,420
Come on.

50
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,060
Make the transfer
to show your sincerity.

51
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:01,900
(Payment Code)

52
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:13,500
Done.

53
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:17,500
(To be received by Lin Miaomiao)

54
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:25,500
I've really seen it all now.

55
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:32,620
Miss Su's got skills
and works hard herself.

56
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:33,700
I think you should

57
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,860
focus more on her emotional needs.

58
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:36,860
Tell me more.

59
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:38,180
Chairman Cen demeaned her.

60
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:40,280
You shouldn't treat her
with just a bit of sweetness.

61
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:41,940
What she needs more is your company.

62
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:43,620
Spend more time by her side.

63
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,220
Like last night, for example.

64
00:03:45,220 --> 00:03:46,120
Or even now.

65
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:47,740
You shouldn't sit here talking with me.

66
