♪All I want is to follow you♪

99
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:17,100
Secretary Lin.

100
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:18,500
What do you want?

101
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:19,860
I'm rushing to work.

102
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,740
Let's talk at the company.

103
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:22,880
Eat breakfast before you go.

104
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:24,660
If I'm late, will you take the fall?

105
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:25,540
I'll take the blame.

106
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:49,380
Here, try this.

107
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:54,580
If Peipei knew

108
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:55,660
I woke up early today

109
00:06:55,660 --> 00:06:57,380
just to make her this breakfast,

110
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:59,100
do you think she'd be touched?

111
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:01,220
The breakfast you made?

112
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:03,100
Isn't this just takeout?

113
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,060
Maybe.

114
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,900
She might even cry happy tears,

115
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,620
then snap a photo, and post it online

116
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:12,940
to let the world know

117
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:14,540
she has such a good boyfriend.

118
00:07:14,780 --> 00:07:15,620
Well.

119
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,920
That's just how much I care for her.

120
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,580
I never tire of making breakfast

121
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:21,940
for the one I love.

122
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:28,020
Thanks to your advice last night,

123
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:29,340
I finally took action.

124
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:30,420
How about this?

125
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:32,180
When the wedding comes,

126
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:33,960
you'll sit at the main table.

127
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,500
You don't need to work today.

128
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,780
I've told my mother already.

129
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:44,740
You'll come with me to the set later

130
00:07:45,890 --> 00:07:47,020
to surprise Peipei.

131
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:48,980
Eat up.

132
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,620
We'll leave in 15 minutes.

133
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:41,540
If you don't drink it, I will.

134
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:49,820
Milk for Peipei always tastes best.

135
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:00,900
Mr. Cen.

136
00:09:01,140 --> 00:09:02,740
All the support gifts are ready.

137
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,820
Now, we await Miss Su's arrival.

138
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:05,680
Well done.

139
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,140
I'll add it to your year-end bonus.

140
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:08,620
Thank you, Mr. Cen.

141
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:11,660
Miaomiao, let me help you with that.

142
00:09:11,660 --> 00:09:12,500
Thank you.

143
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:27,620
(Peipei, be happy!)

144
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:28,780
Still upset?

145
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:33,260
You left me alone last night.

146
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:34,860
I had to deal with my mother.

147
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:36,940
Did you manage it?

148
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:39,300
I made you a full breakfast.

149
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:40,140
Still not enough?

150
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:42,300
No.

151
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,900
Then what will make you happy?

152
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,380
Aren't you going to see her off?

153
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:50,860
Good idea.

154
00:09:51,260 --> 00:09:52,380
You really left?

155
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,460
I was just saying.

156
00:09:58,780 --> 00:09:59,660
I want

157
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:02,700
Secretary Lin to apologize
to me for yesterday.

158
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:06,720
Didn't you say

159
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:08,540
you didn't need her
to apologize yesterday?

160
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:10,260
That was yesterday.

161
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:12,060
Can't you even handle this small task?

162
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:27,900
Stop staring at her.

163
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:30,200
I wasn't staring at her.

164
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:31,700
You clearly kept looking at her.

165
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,860
Stop this.

166
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:35,380
I'm just thinking about how to fix this.

167
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:38,540
I said she should apologize to me.

168
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:40,660
She's my mother's lackey.

169
00:10:40,660 --> 00:10:41,780
You know that.

170
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:43,920
What happened yesterday
was my mother's idea.

171
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:45,820
Let's just let it pass.

172
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:47,420
Don't turn this into a big thing.

173
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:49,980
What if she complains
to my mother again?

174
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:52,500
Aren't we just making things worse?

175
00:10:53,060 --> 00:10:54,900
Why do I feel like you're siding

176
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,100
with her?

177
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:01,460
Fine.

178
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:06,380
What are you two talking about?

179
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:10,580
I'm asking Miaomiao for romance advice.

180
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:11,740
I've been single since birth.

181
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:13,620
I wonder when I'll finally meet someone.

182
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:15,200
Then you should ask for some tips.

183
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:16,700
Secretary Lin knows a lot.

184
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,220
Who said that? Miaomiao just said

185
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,020
she hasn't dated in ages.

186
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:24,220
You must be kidding.

187
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:26,660
I'm serious. She just had one boyfriend.

188
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:29,580
Her first love hurt her deeply.

189
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:30,900
He was a playboy.

190
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,980
Now, she can't trust love anymore.

191
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:35,980
I hope I never run into that jerk.

192
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:39,100
Don't you have many admirers?

193
00:11:39,820 --> 00:11:41,180
Haven't you met the right one?

194
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:42,420
Mr. Cen.

195
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,160
No need to worry
about your employees' private lives.

196
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:47,020
Let's get back to business.

197
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,540
I need a favor.

198
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,860
It's about Miss Su, right?

199
00:11:57,060 --> 00:11:57,900
Yes.

200
00:11:58,340 --> 00:12:00,420
She wants you to apologize
for yesterday.

201
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:03,060
Peipei didn't do anything wrong.

202
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,980
Yet you scolded her so harshly.

203
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:07,220
I felt bad for her.

204
00:12:07,780 --> 00:12:08,900
I feel bad for...

205
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:13,220
I feel bad for my future wife.

206
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:14,060
Is that not allowed?

207
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,700
Future wife?

208
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:16,980
That's right.

209
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:18,460
We're planning to get married.

210
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:27,820
You can't calm her down,

211
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:29,220
so you drag me into this?

212
00:12:29,470 --> 00:12:30,240
Am I just a tool

213
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,620
that you can use wherever you need?

214
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:33,180
When you promised my mother,

215
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,740
why didn't you think of the outcome?

216
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:36,340
I never thought you would...

217
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:37,740
What?

218
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:44,900
I just spoke to her
on behalf of Chairman Cen.

219
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,340
Why am I the one apologizing?

220
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:48,260
Besides,

221
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:50,140
you used to be so carefree about this.

222
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,220
It's always easy to let go.

223
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:52,460
Why is it different this time?

224
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:54,340
Can she be compared to others?

225
00:12:54,620 --> 00:12:55,660
She's different.

226
00:13:02,420 --> 00:13:04,660
Peipei isn't the type to hold grudges.

227
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,180
Just offer her an apology,

228
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:07,380
make peace, and shake hands.

229
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:08,580
Wouldn't that be for the best?

230
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:12,260
Alright.

231
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:16,040
♪From happiness to loneliness♪

232
00:13:16,430 --> 00:13:19,490
♪An ending I couldn't foresee♪

233
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:24,330
♪The love we promised slipped away♪

234
00:13:24,330 --> 00:13:28,240
♪I'm no longer part of your world♪

235
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:31,520
♪I can't make sense of right or wrong♪

236
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:32,660
Secretary Lin.

237
00:13:34,860 --> 00:13:35,780
Miss Su.

238
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:38,300
I was too abrupt yesterday.

239
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:39,940
I owe you an apology.

240
00:13:39,940 --> 00:13:40,780
I'm sorry.

241
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:45,190
♪It never seems enough♪

242
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:48,080
♪What do you want♪

243
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:52,480
♪You once said
you'd rather gaze into my eyes♪

244
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:55,630
♪Than watch the stars and sunset♪

245
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:58,820
♪And you'd treasure every moment♪

246
00:13:58,820 --> 00:14:02,340
♪And try your best to stay with me♪

247
00:14:02,630 --> 00:14:04,870
♪I took it seriously♪

248
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:08,370
♪Your promises were etched in my heart♪

249
00:14:08,370 --> 00:14:13,680
♪All that's left is unforgettable pain♪

250
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:18,080
♪You once said warm winds
and drifting clouds♪

251
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:21,160
♪Could never match your deep affection♪

252
00:14:21,890 --> 00:14:24,440
♪Even if one day♪

253
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:27,890
♪Time would start to turn back♪

254
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,460
♪As we part ways♪

255
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:34,000
♪I can't help but want you to stay♪

256
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:40,000
♪But in the end,
you still have to leave♪
